  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Education for Girls: Malawi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Malawi, girls&#x2019; access to education is low. One in three women is illiterate and of the girls who do enrol in school, few even complete primary education. Link Community Development Scotland (LCDS) and its local partner, Link Community Development Malawi (LCDM), have identified that by improving the collection and use of data, schools can improve their performance and provide a better service to children. Additionally, they will undertake research to find out the impact of late enrolment on girls&#x2019; retention in school and raise community awareness about he importance of girls&#x2019; education. Finally, the partners will work to increase the coordination and activism of mothers&#x2019; groups and female teachers to improve the school environment for girls. As a result of this work, girls in two Districts of Malawi will stay in schools and schools will better serve girls and all children.</narrative>
  </description>
